pauvre pierrot ( aka poor pete ) is an 1892 french short animated film directed by charles-émile reynaud . it consists of 500 individually painted images and lasts about 15 minutes originally . it is one of the first animated films ever made , and alongside le clown et ses chiens and un bon bock was exhibited in october 1892 when charles-émile reynaud opened his théâtre optique at the musée grévin . it was the first film to demonstrate the theatre optique system developed by reynaud in 1888 . pauvre pierrot is also believed to be the first known usage of film perforations . the combined performance of all three films was known as pantomimes lumineuses . these were the first animated pictures publicly exhibited by means of picture bands . reynaud gave the entire presentation himself by manipulating the images .